    <p>
        <strong>Basketball Outreach</strong> Saturdays, Coquina Key Park, 10:30 a.m. Men
        and youth from Calvary Chapel Southside get together with the high school kids in
        the neighborhood for basketball, lunch and a time of sharing from the Bible. Come
        join the fun or contact Jim McFall at 727-543-6343 for more information.
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>Good News Club</strong> Fridays, Lakewood Elementary School, 2-3:30 p.m.
        A team of eight people from Calvary Chapel Southside lead the weekly Sunday school
        style meeting. The current lesson series is on “God’s Character: Doing the Right
        Thing”. Led by Kathy Green, the club started in 2010 with five children and has
        grown to more than 50 children ages Kindergarten through grade 5. For more information
        or to volunteer, contact Kathy at 727-481-3404 or pnutkpr@yahoo.com.
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>Prison Ministry</strong> Calvary Chapel Southside partners with Calvary
        Chapel St. Petersburg to minister at Polk Correctional Institute, the first Friday
        of each month. For security reasons, arrangements must be made in advance by calling
        Dave Dodge at 727-577-7705.
    </p>
